**Summary of fixes:**

| File | Root Cause | Fix |
|------|------------|-----|
| `job_queue.py:18-20` | Race condition: `await` yielded before marking job as processing, allowing concurrent workers to grab same job | Move `job["status"] = "processing"` before the `await` |
| `worker.py:18-19` | Exception caught but `queue.fail()` never called, leaving jobs stuck in `"processing"` state | Add `queue.fail(job["id"], str(e))` call |
